author: Natalia Vargas
title: Enfermos por vapeo pasaron de 78 a 2.939 en menos de tres años, alerta Salud
text:
Entre los años 2022 y 2023, la cantidad de atenciones por trastornos relacionados con el vapeo pasó de 78 a 1.456 personas respectivamente, mientras que para octubre del presente año, la cifra alcanzó las 2.939 personas. Las atenciones corresponden principalmente a adolescentes y adultos jóvenes.
La información fue divulgada este jueves por el Ministerio de Salud, en el marco del anuncio sobre la actualización del protocolo nacional que vigila los trastornos vinculados al uso de dispositivos electrónicos de fumado, con nicotina y sin esta, así como otros productos de tabaco calentado.
Según la institución rectora en salud, este protocolo contribuirá a mejorar el registro de los casos atendidos en los servicios de salud, tanto públicos como privados, con la intención de que esta información se convierta en la base para diseñar y fortalecer políticas públicas orientadas al control de estas sustancias.
LEA MÁS: [¿Qué se sabe –y qué no– de la grave enfermedad pulmonar relacionada con el vapeo?](https://www.nacion.com/ciencia/salud/que-se-sabe-y-que-no-de-la-grave-enfermedad/YVCPA223JJBF5H5K6JTE573KFE/story/)
“Se ha incrementado de manera acelerada y constante, ya que la industria ha logrado posicionar estos dispositivos en el mercado con atractivas estrategias dirigidas especialmente a la población más joven; en dicho grupo, estos productos son promovidos como accesibles e inofensivos”, indicó Salud a través de un comunicado de prensa.
Asimismo, alertó de que, además de contener sustancias dañinas, algunos líquidos poseen concentraciones de nicotina considerablemente mayores que las de un cigarrillo convencional. La institución recordó que la nicotina es altamente adictiva y puede perjudicar el desarrollo cerebral de los adolescentes, el cual se extiende desde los primeros años de vida hasta cerca de los 25 años de edad.
Entre las consecuencias de esta práctica,[ la Caja Costarricense de Seguro Social ha destacado q](https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/salud/enfermos-por-vapeo-pasaron-de-13-a-1456-en-dos/5SBIZR6SUFDG3BR7ZSRHBKCZFM/story/)ue nuevas enfermedades respiratorias se asocian a la inflamación crónica de las vías respiratorias y el tejido pulmonar, y ha identificado un incremento en las enfermedades crónicas no transmisibles.
Como parte de las estrategias para mitigar los efectos del vapeo, el pasado 14 de mayo, el Ministerio de Salud anunció la prohibición inmediata –mediante una resolución– de la importación, el uso, la venta y la comercialización de productos con nicotina sintética.
LEA MÁS: [Salud prohíbe importar, usar y vender productos con nicotina sintética en intento de frenar efectos de vapeo](https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/salud/salud-prohibe-importar-usar-y-vender-productos-con/RPWJ24EKCRCAXERMENLBKRX2YY/story/)
La iniciativa también prohibió la distribución, publicidad, promoción y patrocinio de estos productos, así como de los accesorios destinados a su consumo y administración por cualquier vía de ingreso al organismo. Esta medida rige para establecimientos de todo tipo, incluyendo canales telefónicos, digitales o cualquier otro medio que facilite el acceso a dichos dispositivos y sustancias.
El Ministerio de Salud emitió un recordatorio a la población sobre el uso de estos dispositivos. Resaltó que no son seguros para personas de ninguna edad e instó a evitar la compra de productos de origen clandestino o de procedencia desconocida, además de abstenerse de agregar a estos dispositivos sustancias no indicadas por el fabricante.

author: Nivedita Dash
title: Tamil Nadu: Rains continue to lash parts of state, waterlogging in parts of Tirunelveli reported
text:
Widespread rains continued to lash parts of Tamil Nadu on Friday. Traffic at Kathipara, Poonammallee, Porur, Maduravoyal, Vysarpadi, and Chennai suburbs came to a standstill with all sorts of vehicles getting stranded in the rainwater. Residents of Vyasarpadi and Pallavaram complained that water logging in their areas during monsoon has become a regular feature. Overnight rains lashed Chennai and the neighbouring Tiruvallur, Chengelpet and Kancheepuram, besides Villupuram and some areas in the Cauvery delta region.
Several areas in Thiruvannamalai, which had experienced mud slips atleast four times when Cyclone Fengal crossed the Tamil Nadu and Karaikal coast on November 30, and some parts in the southern districts, as well, were swarmed by swathes of water. An NDRF team has been deployed at Thiruvannamalai, equipped with advanced disaster management equipment to respond to any emergency, an official said.
The state government has urged people in the low-lying areas to remain vigilant and take appropriate action.
Following a sudden increase in the inflows into the Sathanur dam in Thiruvannamalai district that sharply surged the water level, about 13,000 cusecs water was released from the reservoir on Thursday. In Chennai, about 1,000 cusecs water was released from the Poondi dam, one of the chief sources of drinking water to the metro, in the afternoon and the quantum was gradually increased to about 5,000 cusecs in the evening, PWD said. The water level in the Chembarambakkam dam inched towards the full reservoir level. Its present level stood at 21.90 feet against its full level capacity of 24 feet. It’s storage increased to 84.88 percent owing to heavy rain in the catchment areas.

Vivo Warns the Risks of UV-Cured Screen Protectors; Check Vivo's Recommendations
As such, Vivo warns users of potential damage caused by UV-cured screen protectors, encouraging them to embrace proper safety and authorized installation methods.
Vivo has released an important safety notice to mobile phone users on the dangers of UV-cured tempered glass screen protectors. The glass screen protectors are most popular for curved screens, where UV glue is used for secure adhesion. These protectors provide great edge-to-edge coverage, but improper installation and low-quality materials can damage your phone's performance and durability.
Threats of Using UV-Cured Screen Protectors
Vivo highlighted a few problems that could occur in the application of UV glue incorrectly:
Aesthetic and Material Damage: UV glue can harm materials like leather battery covers, causing bulges or peeling, and may lead to paint chipping on the camera frame.
Air Bubble Issues: During application, air bubbles can force glue into sensitive areas such as receivers or side buttons, which can create noise or serve as an operational issue.
Audio Interference: The sound output will become distorted or muffled if it covers the speaker hole.
Button Malfunctions: Adhesive may seep through side buttons and make them sticky, unusable, or sticking and malfunctioning.
SIM Tray and Water Resistance Issues: If glue enters the SIM tray, it can complicate insertion and removal while compromising the phone's water-resistant seals.
Vivo emphasized that damages caused by improper installation, especially by unauthorized technicians, are not covered under the warranty.
Vivo's Recommendations for Protection
Vivo recommends applying authentic screen protectors obtained at its authorized service centres to protect your smartphone. The protectors are custom-designed for each Vivo model, ensuring perfect fitting and maximum protection.
For users choosing UV-cured tempered glass, Vivo advises extra precautions during installation:
Cover sensitive areas like the receiver, side buttons, and SIM tray with the sealing film provided in the packaging.
Avoid applying excessive glue and ensure even spreading to prevent seepage.
Seek professional assistance from authorized service centres to minimize risks.
Why You Should Act Now
Although UV-cured screen protectors add extra shine and feel to the phone, the risks of improper installation outweigh the benefits. Original accessories and adherence to Vivo guidelines ensure protection against long-term damage while maintaining performance and looks. Stay alert and instead opt for safety over shortcuts that will keep your Vivo smartphone in perfect condition.

author: @walbnews10
title: Jackie Robinson Boys and Girls Club of Cairo-Grady County receives $850k grant for expansion project
text:
ALBANY, Ga. (WALB) -The Jackie Robinson Boys & Girls Club (JRBGC) of Cairo-Grady County can now look forward to expanding its facility, thanks to the recent congressional approval of a $850,000 grant.
This transformative grant, named “Project Homerun,” signals a new chapter in the club’s history, promising enhanced opportunities and resources for the youth it serves.
The Bill was approved by the House of Representatives on March 7th, passed by the Senate on March 8th, and ultimately signed into law by the President on March 9th.
The grant proposal was one of 100 submitted throughout the district. Out of these submissions, 15 community projects were chosen for funding, including “Project Homerun”.
The JRBGC is partially funded by the federal government and operates with the support of tax-exempt status. The club relies on various sources for its operating budget. These include membership fees, individual donations, and fundraisers led by board members.
Expansion plans include an indoor gymnasium and additional classroom spaces. “The project is an appropriate use of grant funds because the club has physically outgrown its current location due to space constraints.” says JRBGC Board Chair Donica Douglas. Moving to a second location to serve more local youth has been a goal of the club for years. But, due to flooding concerns that dream was not possible.
The grant received widespread support, with local community leaders writing letters of support.
“We are so very appreciative of the efforts by Congressman Bishop’s office and his staff for helping this project become a reality for the JRBGC” Executive Director Stephen Francis says of the Congressman and Field Representative’s efforts.

text:
8月14日， 联瑞新材 跌2.77%，成交额2.98亿元，换手率2.22%，总市值133.73亿元。
异动分析
先进封装+存储芯片+专精特新
1、2023年6月15日互动易：公司有产品已批量用于半导体的先进封装材料中。
2、根据2025年4月28日公告：公司持续聚焦高端芯片（AI、5G、HPC 等）封装、异构集成先进封装（Chiplet、HBM 等）、新一代高频高速覆铜板（M7、M8、M9等）、新能源汽车用高导热热界面材料、先进毫米波雷达等下游应用领域的先进技术，深化纳米级球形二氧化硅、高性能球形二氧化钛、先进氮化物粉体等功能性粉体材料的研究开发及应用推广，突破了氮化物球化技术、氮化铝防水解等诸多技术难题。
3、专精特新“小巨人”企业是全国中小企业评定工作中最高等级、最具权威的荣誉称号，是指专注于细分市场、创新能力强、市场占有率高、掌握关键核心技术、质量效益优的排头兵企业，对于提升中小企业自身的竞争力，以及提升产业链、供应链稳定性和竞争力具有重大意义。公司已入选工信部专精特新小巨人企业名单。

公司简介
资料显示，江苏联瑞新材料股份有限公司位于江苏省 连云港 市海州区新浦经济开发区，成立日期2002年4月28日，上市日期2019年11月15日，公司主营业务涉及无机填料和颗粒载体行业产品的研发、制造和销售。主营业务收入构成为：球形无机粉体57.16%，角形无机粉体26.39%，其他16.32%，其他(补充)0.12%。
联瑞新材所属申万行业为：基础化工-非金属材料Ⅱ-非金属材料Ⅲ。所属概念板块包括：HBM概念、PCB概念、先进封装、电子化学品、5G等。
截至3月31日，联瑞新材股东户数7952.00，较上期减少7.32%；人均流通股23358股，较上期增加7.90%。2025年1月-3月，联瑞新材实现营业收入2.39亿元，同比增长18.00%；归母净利润6303.77万元，同比增长21.99%。
分红方面，联瑞新材A股上市后累计派现3.81亿元。近三年，累计派现2.42亿元。
机构持仓方面，截止2025年3月31日，联瑞新材十大流通股东中，信澳匠心臻选两年持有期混合（010363）位居第八大流通股东，持股131.67万股，为新进股东。国寿安保智慧生活股票A（001672）位居第十大流通股东，持股103.97万股，为新进股东。景顺长城电子信息产业股票A类（010003）、香港中央结算有限公司退出十大流通股东之列。
